# @dukkani/config Package

## Purpose

The `config` package contains shared TypeScript configuration files used across the monorepo. It ensures consistent TypeScript settings.

## Structure

```
packages/config/
├── tsconfig.base.json      # Base TypeScript configuration
└── tsconfig.nextjs.json    # Next.js-specific configuration
```

## Configuration Files

### Base Configuration
`tsconfig.base.json` - Shared TypeScript settings for all packages

### Next.js Configuration
`tsconfig.nextjs.json` - Next.js-specific TypeScript settings

## Usage

### In Packages

```json
// packages/{package}/tsconfig.json
{
  "extends": "@dukkani/config/tsconfig.base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src"
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*"]
}
```

### In Apps

```json
// apps/{app}/tsconfig.json
{
  "extends": "@dukkani/config/tsconfig.nextjs.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["next-env.d.ts", "**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx", ".next/types/**/*.ts"]
}
```

## Best Practices

- Extend base configuration instead of duplicating settings
- Use path aliases for cleaner imports
- Keep configurations consistent across packages
- Document any package-specific overrides

## Dependencies

None (configuration only)

## Dependents

- All packages and apps (via tsconfig.json extends)
